1
00:00:10,311 --> 00:00:12,733
I think I like Nao.

2
00:00:13,693 --> 00:00:18,109
If you stay here any longer,
you'll be in danger too.

3
00:00:19,432 --> 00:00:20,592
I'll handle it myself.

4
00:00:20,922 --> 00:00:22,047
I've decided.

5
00:00:23,973 --> 00:00:25,515
I'm going to work with my family.

6
00:00:26,370 --> 00:00:28,053
I'll protect everyone myself.

7
00:00:29,173 --> 00:00:30,004
Chat.

8
00:00:32,082 --> 00:00:35,042
- You asshole.
- Long time no see. Still got a big mouth, huh?

9
00:00:36,148 --> 00:00:37,020
You bastard.

10
00:00:37,293 --> 00:00:39,155
Take him. Get him in the car.

11
00:00:40,211 --> 00:00:41,648
Hey, where's Nao?

12
00:00:42,287 --> 00:00:45,197
No idea. I saw him answer a call and leave.

13
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:47,428
Go.

14
00:00:53,229 --> 00:00:54,656
Where the hell did he go?

15
00:01:22,622 --> 00:01:23,911
Hey, have you seen Nao?

16
00:01:26,407 --> 00:01:27,112
Any of you?

17
00:01:32,374 --> 00:01:33,915
Where'd he go?

18
00:01:42,074 --> 00:01:44,708
Singha, get back here. My friend's missing.

19
00:01:45,287 --> 00:01:48,447
At first he wasn't answering, and now his phone's off.

20
00:01:49,730 --> 00:01:51,811
He definitely hasn't gone home. His stuff is still here.

21
00:01:54,808 --> 00:01:57,272
I've looked everywhere, but I can't find him.

22
00:01:58,128 --> 00:01:59,869
Stay where you are. I'm coming.

23
00:02:06,795 --> 00:02:07,485
Singha.

24
00:02:15,284 --> 00:02:16,448
Did you send people to look for him?

25
00:02:16,788 --> 00:02:17,694
I did.

26
00:02:18,321 --> 00:02:19,183
And we found him.

27
00:02:20,205 --> 00:02:20,905
Where is he?

28
00:02:21,395 --> 00:02:22,266
Is he okay?

29
00:02:22,928 --> 00:02:23,977
He's safe now.

30
00:02:24,472 --> 00:02:26,084
They're taking him to the hospital.

31
00:02:26,623 --> 00:02:28,493
How is going to the hospital considered safe?

32
00:02:29,548 --> 00:02:31,528
- Just some minor injuries.
- How minor?

33
00:02:32,217 --> 00:02:34,694
I don't know. You'll see when we get there.

34
00:02:37,862 --> 00:02:39,536
What the hell happened?

35
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:42,564
Huh?

36
00:03:03,671 --> 00:03:04,773
Chat?

37
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:07,005
Have you ever met him?

38
00:03:07,611 --> 00:03:08,456
Never.

39
00:03:10,401 --> 00:03:11,605
All I know is...

40
00:03:11,890 --> 00:03:13,228
he's Aunt Maew's new boyfriend.

41
00:03:13,708 --> 00:03:15,124
The guy who's supposedly in prison.

42
00:03:16,594 --> 00:03:17,928
He wasn't actually in prison.

43
00:03:18,834 --> 00:03:21,660
He was undercover inside and just got out.

44
00:03:25,860 --> 00:03:28,294
He's with the rival side. They don't get along with our gang.

45
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:34,647
I think you should stop getting involved with that family.

46
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:38,650
What do you mean?

47
00:03:44,176 --> 00:03:47,277
Their gang leader is a disgusting old man.

48
00:03:48,005 --> 00:03:49,272
He's into young boys.

49
00:03:51,256 --> 00:03:53,388
Chat probably wants to please the boss...

50
00:03:53,697 --> 00:03:55,583
by offering up those two boys.

51
00:04:09,654 --> 00:04:11,533
Hey, Suer. Where are you going?

52
00:04:14,622 --> 00:04:16,158
Hey! Go after him and stop him now!

53
00:04:41,226 --> 00:04:43,622
Hey, what's that sound? Go check it out.

54
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:06,376
P'Jo.

55
00:05:07,167 --> 00:05:09,434
I need a favor from you.

56
00:05:09,785 --> 00:05:11,120
It's really important.

57
00:05:11,985 --> 00:05:13,422
And I won't ask you for anything ever again.

58
00:05:14,148 --> 00:05:15,260
And what do I get out of it?

59
00:05:16,208 --> 00:05:17,736
I don't have anything to offer right now.

60
00:05:18,752 --> 00:05:19,872
But one day...

61
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:21,854
I'll be useful to you.

62
00:05:22,195 --> 00:05:23,161
I promise.

63
00:05:24,007 --> 00:05:25,284
You'll just be throwing your life away.

64
00:05:25,605 --> 00:05:26,722
There's nothing you can do.

65
00:05:28,127 --> 00:05:29,222
You don't understand.

66
00:05:30,262 --> 00:05:31,518
Do you have someone important to you?

67
00:05:32,657 --> 00:05:34,607
Someone so important that without them,

68
00:05:35,130 --> 00:05:36,834
your life would lose all meaning?

69
00:05:38,859 --> 00:05:43,161
If they needed help, and you were the only one who could help them...

70
00:05:44,294 --> 00:05:45,528
but you only have your own by the way.

71
00:05:50,748 --> 00:05:52,742
Just think of it as helping me before I die.

72
00:05:54,285 --> 00:05:56,032
Let me see Nao for ten minutes.

73
00:05:58,388 --> 00:05:59,437
I'll handle the rest myself.

74
00:06:02,155 --> 00:06:02,989
Fine.

75
00:06:03,287 --> 00:06:05,672
I'll have someone take you to Duennao...

76
00:06:06,002 --> 00:06:07,259
without your brother finding out.

77
00:06:10,022 --> 00:06:11,025
One more thing.

78
00:06:12,259 --> 00:06:13,742
I need some information.

79
00:06:14,831 --> 00:06:16,103
What is he doing, and where is he?

80
00:06:16,697 --> 00:06:17,875
I'll take care of it.

81
00:06:18,297 --> 00:06:20,047
Consider it your dying gift.

82
00:06:20,534 --> 00:06:22,306
I'll send one of my men with you.

83
00:06:22,902 --> 00:06:24,213
But if things go south,

84
00:06:24,653 --> 00:06:26,088
I'm not letting my guy risk his life for you.

85
00:06:28,847 --> 00:06:29,657
Thank you so much.

86
00:08:27,342 --> 00:08:28,478
Change into this and follow me.

87
00:08:34,445 --> 00:08:37,623
Just act natural.
Pretend you're observing the patient's condition.

88
00:08:37,776 --> 00:08:38,760
I'll do the examination myself.

89
00:08:39,186 --> 00:08:40,917
You really are a nurse, right?

90
00:08:41,394 --> 00:08:43,580
Yes. I used to examine patients.

91
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:47,493
I've been instructed to get you past the guards and into the room.

92
00:08:47,835 --> 00:08:50,607
Those guards should recognize me, so there shouldn't be any problems.

93
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:54,828
I just want to check on Duennao.

94
00:08:55,859 --> 00:08:57,120
I'm not going to do anything else.

95
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:00,888
But no one will recognize you, right?

96
00:09:02,928 --> 00:09:04,065
Is Singha here?

97
00:09:04,998 --> 00:09:06,072
Just the guards.

98
00:09:14,534 --> 00:09:15,936
We're here for the daily checkup.

99
00:09:16,438 --> 00:09:17,219
Wait.

100
00:09:17,665 --> 00:09:18,856
Take off your mask.

101
00:09:19,971 --> 00:09:23,647
Cannot. It won't be safe for the patient and all of us.

102
00:09:24,339 --> 00:09:25,838
Mr. Leo ordered us to check everyone.

103
00:09:26,257 --> 00:09:27,844
In case Tiger tries to sneak in.

104
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,134
You mean Tiger...

105
00:09:36,357 --> 00:09:37,731
Does he look like this?

106
00:09:41,056 --> 00:09:41,937
Where did you see him?

107
00:09:43,552 --> 00:09:45,734
I happened to spot him behind the hospital just now.

108
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,228
You two, come with me.

109
00:09:47,362 --> 00:09:48,401
You stay here and keep watch.

110
00:09:48,654 --> 00:09:49,428
Let's go.

111
00:09:51,866 --> 00:09:55,500
Then we'd better get inside quickly.
It'll be bad if we don't change the IV bag in time.

112
00:09:55,896 --> 00:09:57,691
The doctor also needs to check a few things.

113
00:10:15,927 --> 00:10:16,786
Nao.

114
00:10:24,114 --> 00:10:25,060
Do you know...

115
00:10:25,419 --> 00:10:26,053
when he'll wake up?

116
00:10:26,798 --> 00:10:28,456
I don't think it'll be later than tomorrow.

117
00:10:30,552 --> 00:10:31,482
What about the other two?

118
00:10:32,312 --> 00:10:34,521
Those two are in better condition than Mr. Duennao.

119
00:10:34,918 --> 00:10:38,035
The woman regained consciousness once about an hour ago.

120
00:10:38,463 --> 00:10:40,435
But she was disoriented and couldn't speak yet.

121
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:04,900
You're gonna be okay.

122
00:11:32,472 --> 00:11:33,826
I'll protect you myself.

123
00:11:35,034 --> 00:11:36,032
I promise.

124
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,176
To Duennao,

125
00:11:48,474 --> 00:11:50,511
If you're reading this letter,

126
00:11:51,475 --> 00:11:52,505
then I'm probably gone.

127
00:11:54,031 --> 00:11:55,900
Whatever I died from,

128
00:11:57,562 --> 00:11:58,743
don't go looking into it.

129
00:12:00,371 --> 00:12:01,260
Don't even try to find out.

130
00:12:03,488 --> 00:12:06,813
I just want you to know it was my own choice.

131
00:12:18,020 --> 00:12:19,552
The reason I left this letter...

132
00:12:20,711 --> 00:12:22,225
is because I wanted to tell you...

133
00:12:24,660 --> 00:12:27,717
thank you for everything.

134
00:12:29,663 --> 00:12:33,826
Ever since you came into my life, you've completely changed it.

135
00:12:35,007 --> 00:12:39,235
I've never met anyone so naive and trusting before.

136
00:12:42,829 --> 00:12:46,485
Someone who's sharp-tongued, but actually incredibly kind.

137
00:12:49,844 --> 00:12:55,614
Someone who sings off-key, laughs too loud,
eats messily, and talks nonsense all the time.

138
00:12:55,894 --> 00:12:57,167
But being with you...

139
00:12:57,573 --> 00:12:58,880
is so damn fun.

140
00:13:00,050 --> 00:13:01,595
I've never had this much fun before.

141
00:13:02,798 --> 00:13:06,782
It's crazy, isn't it? We haven't even known each other for a year.

142
00:13:07,645 --> 00:13:09,051
But I love you this much.

143
00:13:10,225 --> 00:13:13,328
Not the way a friend does.

144
00:13:14,613 --> 00:13:17,601
I wonder if you know.
Though if I had to guess...

145
00:13:17,957 --> 00:13:19,826
you probably don't. You're too clueless.

146
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,137
Hey!

147
00:14:40,111 --> 00:14:41,142
Who are you?

148
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:43,968
Who sent you?

149
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:46,922
Sir.

150
00:14:47,690 --> 00:14:49,951
I know where my son is now.

151
00:15:02,865 --> 00:15:06,099
But now I know for sure that I love you.

152
00:15:08,463 --> 00:15:09,309
You!

153
00:15:11,847 --> 00:15:13,294
I love you so damn much.

154
00:15:13,805 --> 00:15:17,743
Even if you don't feel the same, that's okay.

155
00:15:18,570 --> 00:15:19,797
But honestly...

156
00:15:20,348 --> 00:15:22,100
I wish I could see your face when you find out.

157
00:15:23,028 --> 00:15:24,770
I hope your life is full of smiles.

158
00:15:25,734 --> 00:15:29,090
Because when you smile, you're ridiculously cute.

159
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:32,450
Love you so much,
Suer

160
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:02,242
Suer.

161
00:16:03,106 --> 00:16:04,327
I'm sorry.

162
00:16:05,004 --> 00:16:06,645
I'm sorry, Suer.

163
00:16:10,628 --> 00:16:11,841
How many days has it been?

164
00:16:13,468 --> 00:16:14,800
Seven days.

165
00:16:42,362 --> 00:16:43,437
How's Nao?

166
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:47,322
He's safe now.

167
00:16:48,637 --> 00:16:51,077
Don't worry. Nao doesn't know anything.

168
00:16:54,106 --> 00:16:55,174
What do you mean?

169
00:16:55,714 --> 00:16:57,514
I had someone pose as a police officer.

170
00:16:58,685 --> 00:17:00,337
We fabricated evidence.

171
00:17:01,967 --> 00:17:06,262
- We told him Chat was the kidnapper.
- That's all I have to report.

172
00:17:06,668 --> 00:17:08,136
They've all been arrested.

173
00:17:08,717 --> 00:17:09,668
Get well soon.

174
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:12,734
Back then, your friend was so badly injured that he passed out.

175
00:17:13,823 --> 00:17:15,995
When he woke up, he could barely remember anything.

176
00:17:16,080 --> 00:17:18,965
- You'll be able to go home soon, dear.
- So he believed everything I made up.

177
00:17:28,792 --> 00:17:29,709
Suer.

178
00:17:31,722 --> 00:17:34,269
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

179
00:17:34,844 --> 00:17:37,128
I just didn't want you getting involved with those people.

180
00:17:39,413 --> 00:17:41,586
I was only worrying about you in my own way.

181
00:17:43,834 --> 00:17:45,816
I never stopped to think about what you wanted.

182
00:17:47,831 --> 00:17:50,068
I'm sorry I got there too late to help you.

183
00:17:53,607 --> 00:17:54,637
You came to save me?

184
00:17:55,860 --> 00:17:56,561
Yeah.

185
00:17:57,837 --> 00:17:59,641
But by the time I got there, you were already unconscious.

186
00:18:01,884 --> 00:18:02,797
Still...

187
00:18:03,297 --> 00:18:06,585
you managed to kill the gang leader and Chat.

188
00:18:07,805 --> 00:18:09,250
You're unbelievable.

189
00:18:09,794 --> 00:18:11,333
You're amazing.

190
00:18:12,085 --> 00:18:13,660
That's my little brother.

191
00:18:15,854 --> 00:18:18,238
You said you were worried about me, but you don't seem worried about hurting me at all.

192
00:18:22,727 --> 00:18:24,459
It's all over now, right?

193
00:18:26,148 --> 00:18:27,878
Duennao's safe now, right?

194
00:18:32,355 --> 00:18:34,260
They probably won't bother your friend anymore.

195
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:38,354
Is that kid really that important to you?

196
00:18:41,093 --> 00:18:42,605
Just look at everything you've done.

197
00:18:42,917 --> 00:18:44,459
And look at the state you're in now.

198
00:18:53,847 --> 00:18:55,680
Dad's really angry right now.

199
00:18:56,829 --> 00:18:58,703
He said he's sending you to Hong Kong.

200
00:19:03,971 --> 00:19:04,693
Mm.

201
00:19:08,592 --> 00:19:09,825
You're giving in that easily?

202
00:19:13,165 --> 00:19:14,714
If they send me to Hong Kong...

203
00:19:16,703 --> 00:19:17,748
will I become stronger?

204
00:19:19,928 --> 00:19:21,391
Will I be able to protect Duennao?

205
00:19:23,202 --> 00:19:24,074
Of course you will.

206
00:19:27,795 --> 00:19:28,400
Oh, right.

207
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:31,014
There's a letter...

208
00:19:32,722 --> 00:19:33,819
for you.

209
00:19:47,568 --> 00:19:48,720
Burn it for me too.

210
00:19:51,798 --> 00:19:52,440
Hey.

211
00:19:53,357 --> 00:19:54,450
Don't read it, okay?

212
00:19:56,051 --> 00:19:56,804
Yeah.

213
00:20:00,266 --> 00:20:01,044
Singha.

214
00:20:03,216 --> 00:20:04,317
Can I borrow your phone?

215
00:20:21,376 --> 00:20:22,205
Hello?

216
00:20:22,474 --> 00:20:23,205
Nao.

217
00:20:24,225 --> 00:20:25,023
How are you doing?

218
00:20:25,930 --> 00:20:28,268
- Uh... who is this?
- It's me.

219
00:20:28,607 --> 00:20:30,758
Suer. Don't you recognize my voice?

220
00:20:31,632 --> 00:20:32,680
Suer!

221
00:20:33,324 --> 00:20:35,979
Where the hell have you been? You didn't tell me anything.

222
00:20:36,251 --> 00:20:37,320
And where are you now?

223
00:20:37,709 --> 00:20:38,680
Are you okay?

224
00:20:40,294 --> 00:20:41,597
I'm in Hong Kong.

225
00:20:42,715 --> 00:20:43,459
What?

226
00:20:43,835 --> 00:20:44,802
Hong Kong?

227
00:20:45,177 --> 00:20:46,188
What are you doing there?

228
00:20:47,379 --> 00:20:48,625
I came with my family.

229
00:20:50,933 --> 00:20:52,422
For family business?

230
00:20:54,158 --> 00:20:56,214
You seriously couldn't have told me first?

231
00:20:58,022 --> 00:20:59,149
Sorry.

232
00:20:59,540 --> 00:21:00,638
It was...

233
00:21:01,032 --> 00:21:02,145
so sudden.

234
00:21:03,238 --> 00:21:04,797
I even forgot to bring my phone.

235
00:21:05,561 --> 00:21:07,093
It took me a while...

236
00:21:08,494 --> 00:21:10,050
before I could contact you.

237
00:21:10,946 --> 00:21:14,405
Yeah, at first I was wondering where you'd disappeared to.

238
00:21:14,748 --> 00:21:15,989
You weren't replying to my messages.

239
00:21:16,288 --> 00:21:18,783
You wouldn't answer your phone, and you weren't showing up at school.

240
00:21:19,419 --> 00:21:21,988
I asked Mick and Field, but they had no idea where you'd gone either.

241
00:21:22,601 --> 00:21:24,604
So you're really there for family business, right?

242
00:21:25,511 --> 00:21:26,983
Did you leave right after the competition?

243
00:21:28,028 --> 00:21:28,842
Yeah.

244
00:21:29,706 --> 00:21:31,462
They took me there as soon as it ended.

245
00:21:32,891 --> 00:21:34,084
What about school?

246
00:21:36,751 --> 00:21:38,570
Uh, I'm at home.

247
00:21:39,281 --> 00:21:41,536
I clumsily fell down the stairs, damn it.

248
00:21:42,152 --> 00:21:44,109
So my mom made me stay home and rest.

249
00:21:44,517 --> 00:21:45,570
How about you?

250
00:21:46,275 --> 00:21:49,748
Honestly, I could've gone to school, but my mom was worried,

251
00:21:50,191 --> 00:21:51,552
so she made me stay home.

252
00:21:51,991 --> 00:21:53,475
So when are you coming back?

253
00:21:58,226 --> 00:21:59,293
I don't know.

254
00:22:00,355 --> 00:22:01,400
Maybe a year.

255
00:22:01,894 --> 00:22:03,644
What? A whole year?

256
00:22:05,066 --> 00:22:06,965
I thought you'd only be gone for a week or two.

257
00:22:07,531 --> 00:22:08,835
A whole year?

258
00:22:09,284 --> 00:22:11,360
Maybe even longer.

259
00:22:11,906 --> 00:22:13,013
I really don't know.

260
00:22:14,394 --> 00:22:16,487
What about your studies then?

261
00:22:18,321 --> 00:22:19,413
My brother already arranged it.

262
00:22:20,223 --> 00:22:22,401
I'm going as an exchange student instead.

263
00:22:23,434 --> 00:22:25,983
Tell the others that too. Tell them I'm an exchange student.

264
00:22:27,022 --> 00:22:29,078
Yeah, sure. I'll let them know.

265
00:22:29,816 --> 00:22:31,293
So that's it? You're really going?

266
00:22:31,634 --> 00:22:34,693
When you come back, are you gonna be a full-fledged mafia boss or what, Suer?

267
00:22:35,114 --> 00:22:36,398
Not that much.

268
00:22:39,208 --> 00:22:40,343
What a shame.

269
00:22:41,737 --> 00:22:43,364
I won't get to celebrate your birthday with you.

270
00:22:45,367 --> 00:22:46,620
It's okay.

271
00:22:47,293 --> 00:22:49,481
Birthdays aren't a big deal anyway.

272
00:22:52,737 --> 00:22:53,659
Hey, Nao.

273
00:22:56,084 --> 00:22:57,931
I'm here all alone.

274
00:22:59,475 --> 00:23:01,282
I think I'm gonna get pretty lonely.

275
00:23:02,552 --> 00:23:04,299
I won't have anyone to talk to.

276
00:23:06,151 --> 00:23:07,703
Can I...

277
00:23:09,906 --> 00:23:11,493
call you sometimes?

278
00:23:12,728 --> 00:23:13,875
Sure.

279
00:23:14,244 --> 00:23:15,382
I'm free anyway.

280
00:23:16,973 --> 00:23:18,962
Whenever you're lonely, just call me.

281
00:23:19,397 --> 00:23:20,635
I'll keep you company.

282
00:23:22,708 --> 00:23:23,411
Mm.

283
00:23:36,143 --> 00:23:37,303
You like him that much?

284
00:23:41,238 --> 00:23:42,865
It's way beyond just liking him.

285
00:23:43,354 --> 00:23:44,408
Just look at me.

286
00:23:46,235 --> 00:23:46,928
Why do you ask?

287
00:23:51,634 --> 00:23:52,962
Why do you love him so much?

288
00:23:56,613 --> 00:23:58,032
That's a hard question.

289
00:23:59,564 --> 00:24:00,528
Look at you.

290
00:24:01,533 --> 00:24:03,182
- Huh?
- Yeah.

291
00:24:04,650 --> 00:24:06,469
You act all annoying toward me,

292
00:24:06,862 --> 00:24:08,245
but you're actually worried about me.

293
00:24:11,371 --> 00:24:13,601
When I woke up and saw you crying,

294
00:24:13,991 --> 00:24:15,423
I thought I was dreaming.

295
00:24:16,951 --> 00:24:19,530
You've spent years cursing me and messing with me.

296
00:24:19,688 --> 00:24:21,696
Then the moment I almost die, you start crying.

297
00:24:22,103 --> 00:24:23,417
You're such a tsundere.

298
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:29,737
Hey, Singha! I was kidding. Where are you going?

299
00:24:49,020 --> 00:24:50,585
Hey Suer!

300
00:24:50,780 --> 00:24:51,725
What are you doing?

301
00:24:51,928 --> 00:24:53,930
- How are you?
- How's my room?

302
00:24:54,967 --> 00:24:55,610
Hey.

303
00:24:56,330 --> 00:24:57,066
Cool, right?

304
00:24:58,551 --> 00:24:59,795
Your room looks awesome.

305
00:25:01,205 --> 00:25:03,238
Man, I wanna go to Hong Kong too.

306
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:05,448
I've never been there.

307
00:25:06,777 --> 00:25:08,765
Says the guy who's out there having fun.

308
00:25:08,922 --> 00:25:10,888
You left me here studying all by myself.

309
00:25:10,948 --> 00:25:14,767
Hang in there. If you don't understand something, just ask Nue.

310
00:25:40,940 --> 00:25:43,000
Study your enemy well before making a move.

311
00:25:43,725 --> 00:25:45,254
And keep training hard.

312
00:25:54,059 --> 00:25:57,931
Happy birthday to you~

313
00:25:59,549 --> 00:26:00,943
Happy birthday, sweetheart.

314
00:26:00,998 --> 00:26:02,595
- Mom, thank you.
- You're welcome.

315
00:26:02,930 --> 00:26:05,277
- This is from Tiger, sweetheart.
- Thank you.

316
00:26:07,669 --> 00:26:08,968
It's huge, Mom.

317
00:26:09,546 --> 00:26:11,737
Whoa, a watch!

318
00:26:12,077 --> 00:26:14,180
- Wow.
- It's beautiful.

319
00:26:14,241 --> 00:26:15,497
A new pair of shoes.

320
00:26:16,863 --> 00:26:19,328
- Mom!
- Do you like it, sweetheart?

321
00:26:19,530 --> 00:26:21,401
- You bought me a guitar?
- Mm-hmm.

322
00:26:21,758 --> 00:26:24,192
- Try it, try it.
- I've wanted one for so long.

323
00:26:24,280 --> 00:26:25,102
Go ahead.

324
00:26:31,903 --> 00:26:35,014
Shouldn't you tune it before playing, Nao?

325
00:26:39,077 --> 00:26:40,868
Come on, play something.

326
00:26:43,514 --> 00:26:44,389
Can you even play?

327
00:26:44,528 --> 00:26:45,721
Not too badly.

328
00:26:53,605 --> 00:26:55,700
Dan, Suer is calling.

329
00:26:55,828 --> 00:26:57,693
Tiger? How are you doing?

330
00:26:57,825 --> 00:26:58,949
Are you okay?

331
00:26:59,004 --> 00:27:00,583
Yeah, he's doing fine.

332
00:27:00,629 --> 00:27:02,364
Want to talk to Mom?

333
00:27:02,382 --> 00:27:03,108
Mom.

334
00:27:05,325 --> 00:27:07,465
Hi, sweetheart. Are you doing well?

335
00:27:07,616 --> 00:27:08,717
Hi, Mom.

336
00:27:09,548 --> 00:27:11,160
You've lost quite a bit of weight.

337
00:27:12,462 --> 00:27:15,582
I've been exercising a lot lately.

338
00:27:16,078 --> 00:27:17,952
Come back soon and eat my cooking.

339
00:27:18,453 --> 00:27:19,440
Yes, ma'am.

340
00:27:58,001 --> 00:27:59,857
- Have you eaten yet?
- Yes, Mom.

341
00:28:00,447 --> 00:28:01,370
I have to go to class now.

342
00:28:01,404 --> 00:28:05,053
Okay. Study hard, sweetheart.

343
00:28:05,961 --> 00:28:06,496
Let's go.

344
00:28:24,720 --> 00:28:26,253
- Duen.
- Hmm?

345
00:28:26,798 --> 00:28:28,448
Are you calling Tiger tonight?

346
00:28:28,955 --> 00:28:29,925
Tonight?

347
00:28:30,684 --> 00:28:32,065
He said he'd call.

348
00:28:34,389 --> 00:28:36,177
Feels like you guys have been talking less lately.

349
00:28:36,631 --> 00:28:37,976
Did you have a fight or something?

350
00:28:41,057 --> 00:28:41,872
No.

351
00:28:42,601 --> 00:28:44,333
He said he's been busy lately.

352
00:28:45,062 --> 00:28:46,777
Besides, we don't usually call every day.

353
00:28:47,032 --> 00:28:51,142
Yeah, not every day, but never more than three days apart.

354
00:28:52,469 --> 00:28:53,426
Yeah.

355
00:28:54,111 --> 00:28:54,965
Why?

356
00:28:56,217 --> 00:28:56,906
Duen.

357
00:28:57,349 --> 00:28:59,906
Is Tiger a good friend?

358
00:29:00,657 --> 00:29:02,188
Suer?

359
00:29:03,725 --> 00:29:04,517
Yeah, he is.

360
00:29:06,331 --> 00:29:07,508
Why, Dan?

361
00:29:08,063 --> 00:29:10,380
What if another friend said they were lonely too...

362
00:29:10,571 --> 00:29:13,040
and asked to call you every day like that?

363
00:29:15,894 --> 00:29:17,371
I'd probably be on a call with Suer.

364
00:29:18,736 --> 00:29:19,850
Mm.

365
00:29:22,484 --> 00:29:23,918
Maybe we'd all talk together.

366
00:29:25,124 --> 00:29:27,389
Or I'd just let the two of them talk.

367
00:29:27,570 --> 00:29:28,971
A lonely person talking to another lonely person.

368
00:29:35,638 --> 00:29:38,571
Has Tiger told you much about his exchange program?

369
00:29:39,314 --> 00:29:41,014
He says it's pretty fun.

370
00:29:41,404 --> 00:29:42,539
He's gotten to experience lots of new things too.

371
00:29:45,688 --> 00:29:46,751
Sounds fun.

372
00:29:48,423 --> 00:29:50,555
Why? Do you want to go, Dan?

373
00:29:51,241 --> 00:29:52,134
No.

374
00:29:52,694 --> 00:29:54,607
You're such a bad liar, Dan.

375
00:29:54,900 --> 00:29:57,552
I saw you secretly looking it up on the computer.

376
00:29:57,727 --> 00:30:00,448
How did you see that? I deleted everything.

377
00:30:00,893 --> 00:30:02,155
I saw all of it.

378
00:30:03,604 --> 00:30:04,776
But if you get the chance,

379
00:30:05,146 --> 00:30:06,405
you should go.

380
00:30:06,905 --> 00:30:08,114
Don't worry about us.

381
00:30:08,776 --> 00:30:12,545
Mom's already prepared herself for the two of us leaving for university.

382
00:30:12,835 --> 00:30:14,085
She's going to be so lonely.

383
00:30:14,242 --> 00:30:17,416
Yeah, but I'll come back and visit her often, okay?

384
00:30:19,219 --> 00:30:22,048
Then I'll do my best to win that scholarship.

385
00:30:22,878 --> 00:30:24,561
If I don't get one, I won't go.

386
00:30:25,007 --> 00:30:26,822
Mm. Then make sure you get it.

387
00:30:39,432 --> 00:30:40,343
Hey.

388
00:30:41,383 --> 00:30:42,724
Damn, I almost won.

389
00:30:43,794 --> 00:30:46,774
So, Nue wants to study abroad?

390
00:30:47,074 --> 00:30:47,928
Yeah.

391
00:30:48,530 --> 00:30:50,308
But I don't think Dan will go.

392
00:30:51,240 --> 00:30:52,582
Because he's worried about home?

393
00:30:54,551 --> 00:30:57,496
- Dan worries too much.
- Just like you.

394
00:30:57,909 --> 00:30:59,109
You should try...

395
00:30:59,579 --> 00:31:00,696
talking to him.

396
00:31:01,017 --> 00:31:02,531
Tell him he's got me too.

397
00:31:03,579 --> 00:31:06,386
Yeah, you've got him. When are you coming back anyway?

398
00:31:07,398 --> 00:31:08,223
I don't know.

399
00:31:08,933 --> 00:31:10,291
Though it's kinda nice without you around.

400
00:31:10,555 --> 00:31:13,022
My color team might actually win Sports Day this year.

401
00:31:16,038 --> 00:31:18,368
What? I was kidding.

402
00:31:20,502 --> 00:31:21,545
You overthink too much.

403
00:31:29,165 --> 00:31:30,263
Wait here, Mom.

404
00:31:33,257 --> 00:31:34,414
Are you excited, honey?

405
00:31:35,468 --> 00:31:38,247
Not even a little. You seem more excited than I am.

406
00:31:38,438 --> 00:31:39,597
Wow.

407
00:31:39,807 --> 00:31:41,960
Well, I'm here to watch my son compete.

408
00:31:43,637 --> 00:31:46,773
Look at that. He must be tiring in this heat.

409
00:31:50,705 --> 00:31:51,804
They're adorable, Mom.

410
00:31:59,417 --> 00:32:02,240
Nao, make sure you drink plenty of water.

411
00:32:02,358 --> 00:32:05,245
It's so hot. You might pass out.

412
00:32:05,491 --> 00:32:06,554
Got it.

413
00:32:06,804 --> 00:32:09,072
- I'll go get ready now.
- Good luck, Nao.

414
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:11,677
- Good luck, sweetheart.
- Thanks.

415
00:32:12,960 --> 00:32:14,407
- Go win it all.
- Yes, Mom.

416
00:32:14,551 --> 00:32:15,328
See you later.

417
00:32:24,357 --> 00:32:25,800
Khem, aren't you sweating?

418
00:32:26,900 --> 00:32:27,829
It's freaking hot.

419
00:32:28,811 --> 00:32:31,620
But you look kinda cute from the outside, man.

420
00:32:32,700 --> 00:32:34,111
Just kidding.

421
00:32:37,056 --> 00:32:38,035
Look at Mhen over there.

422
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:40,454
He won't even take the head off.

423
00:32:43,360 --> 00:32:45,121
Hey, Mhen. Taking a break?

424
00:32:50,183 --> 00:32:52,438
Yeah. Thanks, man.

425
00:32:54,220 --> 00:32:56,717
Why won't you take the head off? Aren't you hot?

426
00:32:58,748 --> 00:33:00,038
What's your problem? Why aren't you talking to me?

427
00:33:01,225 --> 00:33:02,213
Whatever.

428
00:33:04,251 --> 00:33:05,060
Hey.

429
00:33:05,666 --> 00:33:06,543
Khem.

430
00:33:06,685 --> 00:33:08,176
Do you know that purple team's cheerleader?

431
00:33:08,263 --> 00:33:10,474
Damn, she's cute. Do you know her name?

432
00:33:14,305 --> 00:33:15,251
You asshole, Mhen.

433
00:33:16,054 --> 00:33:17,915
Why'd you smack me on the head, jackass?

434
00:33:18,348 --> 00:33:20,302
You won't talk to me, and now you're hitting me too?

435
00:33:21,632 --> 00:33:22,696
I'm done talking to you.

436
00:33:23,029 --> 00:33:24,133
Hey, Khem.

437
00:33:33,694 --> 00:33:34,988
What's with those two?

438
00:33:40,121 --> 00:33:42,062
That tiger's following you around, honey.

439
00:33:45,389 --> 00:33:46,463
Just ignore him, Mom.

440
00:33:47,841 --> 00:33:50,619
Mom, this is my favorite place.

441
00:33:50,884 --> 00:33:52,327
I eat here every day for lunch.

442
00:33:52,474 --> 00:33:53,958
Let me see.

443
00:33:54,391 --> 00:33:56,034
Is it as good as you said?

444
00:34:00,871 --> 00:34:03,037
It's delicious. I really like it.

445
00:34:03,785 --> 00:34:05,240
Do you like it a lot, Mom?

446
00:34:05,607 --> 00:34:07,927
I sure do. I like it very much.

447
00:34:09,697 --> 00:34:11,173
Very much.

448
00:34:18,201 --> 00:34:19,077
Oh.

449
00:34:19,588 --> 00:34:20,709
That phrase from earlier...

450
00:34:21,077 --> 00:34:22,371
It's Northern dialect.

451
00:34:22,832 --> 00:34:24,177
It means "like a lot."

452
00:34:44,145 --> 00:34:46,004
- Hello?
- Nao.

453
00:34:46,253 --> 00:34:47,425
Are you still at school?

454
00:34:47,817 --> 00:34:49,145
Yeah. Why?

455
00:34:49,274 --> 00:34:52,145
Sorry, but could you run the marathon for us?

456
00:34:52,195 --> 00:34:54,681
The guy who was supposed to run got injured during warm-up.

457
00:34:54,964 --> 00:34:57,299
Out of everyone left, you're probably the best runner.

458
00:34:58,571 --> 00:34:59,884
If you're putting it like that,

459
00:35:00,034 --> 00:35:01,496
I can't really say no, can I?

460
00:35:02,681 --> 00:35:03,930
Sure. What time?

461
00:35:05,986 --> 00:35:07,357
Around 2:30 p.m.

462
00:35:08,514 --> 00:35:10,524
Okay. I'll do it. No problem.

463
00:35:26,339 --> 00:35:27,355
What's up, Mom?

464
00:35:28,771 --> 00:35:30,500
We got an order for boxed meals.

465
00:35:30,721 --> 00:35:32,911
The pay is good, so I accepted it.

466
00:35:35,650 --> 00:35:38,198
Dan, could you come home and help me?

467
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:39,684
Sure, Mom.

468
00:35:40,069 --> 00:35:41,204
Duen.

469
00:35:41,420 --> 00:35:44,832
- I'm sorry, sweetheart.
- It's okay, Mom.

470
00:35:45,128 --> 00:35:46,315
I'll head back as soon as the race is over.

471
00:35:46,625 --> 00:35:47,580
Right away.

472
00:35:49,822 --> 00:35:50,638
Okay.

473
00:35:52,865 --> 00:35:53,767
You're the sweetest.

474
00:35:55,284 --> 00:35:56,872
Let's finish our meal then.

475
00:36:20,060 --> 00:36:21,817
Hey, Mhen. I'm heading home.

476
00:36:22,084 --> 00:36:22,948
See you.

477
00:36:38,605 --> 00:36:39,733
Why are you following me?

478
00:36:49,020 --> 00:36:49,862
Mhen.

479
00:36:50,413 --> 00:36:52,121
You can stop following me now.

480
00:36:55,509 --> 00:36:58,524
Seriously, take that head off and talk to me.

481
00:37:00,805 --> 00:37:02,934
What's wrong with you? Why won't you talk to me?

482
00:37:04,697 --> 00:37:05,337
Ow.

483
00:37:05,595 --> 00:37:07,201
Stop following me.

484
00:37:11,220 --> 00:37:13,702
What the hell is your problem?

485
00:37:14,266 --> 00:37:16,041
Let me punch you just once.

486
00:37:16,339 --> 00:37:19,198
I'm hot. You can hug me later.

487
00:37:19,374 --> 00:37:20,731
What do you even want to talk about?

488
00:37:20,832 --> 00:37:21,819
Hey, Mhen.

489
00:37:24,601 --> 00:37:25,456
Mhen.

490
00:37:35,370 --> 00:37:36,179
Shit.

491
00:37:39,908 --> 00:37:42,315
Help! Somebody help!

492
00:37:44,484 --> 00:37:45,931
Why are you following me?

493
00:37:51,491 --> 00:37:52,352
Who the hell are you?

494
00:37:54,490 --> 00:37:56,825
Ow! That's enough.

495
00:37:56,925 --> 00:37:58,200
Nao, it's me.

496
00:38:03,423 --> 00:38:04,324
Ow.

497
00:38:08,151 --> 00:38:09,848
Holy shit, Suer.

498
00:38:11,336 --> 00:38:12,354
I missed you, man.

499
00:38:14,053 --> 00:38:15,826
When did you get back? Why didn't you tell me?

500
00:38:17,047 --> 00:38:18,035
Hold this for me.

501
00:38:22,392 --> 00:38:24,154
What the hell are you wearing?

502
00:38:24,466 --> 00:38:26,365
- A tiger mascot?
- A cat.

503
00:38:26,696 --> 00:38:28,597
Dude, that's my mom.

504
00:38:33,262 --> 00:38:35,811
Sorry, man. You scared the hell out of me.

505
00:38:36,536 --> 00:38:37,420
It's fine.

506
00:38:39,893 --> 00:38:41,619
First time we meet, you punch me.

507
00:38:42,074 --> 00:38:43,865
Second time in two years, you punch me again.

508
00:38:44,407 --> 00:38:46,346
Why didn't you tell me you were coming back?

509
00:38:47,478 --> 00:38:48,863
I wanted to surprise you.

510
00:38:49,272 --> 00:38:51,611
So I borrowed Mhen's mascot costume.

511
00:38:52,294 --> 00:38:53,918
Well? Surprised?

512
00:38:54,960 --> 00:38:58,785
I was terrified, asshole.
That thing was creepy as hell.

513
00:38:59,094 --> 00:39:01,229
Looked like you were pulling something out earlier.

514
00:39:01,743 --> 00:39:02,945
At first I thought it was a gun.

515
00:39:04,228 --> 00:39:05,702
Nah, this.

516
00:39:06,096 --> 00:39:06,957
I got it for you.

517
00:39:10,034 --> 00:39:11,294
Poor thing.

518
00:39:12,711 --> 00:39:13,745
It's totally crushed now.

519
00:39:14,685 --> 00:39:15,814
Then keep it.

520
00:39:17,988 --> 00:39:20,124
Even all beat up, it's still beautiful.

521
00:39:22,351 --> 00:39:23,767
You like it that much?

522
00:39:25,530 --> 00:39:27,552
Yeah. I really do.

523
00:39:39,225 --> 00:39:40,891
Back from delivering the meals, son?

524
00:39:41,154 --> 00:39:42,337
All done.

525
00:39:42,616 --> 00:39:44,900
How was it? Tired?

526
00:39:45,730 --> 00:39:48,465
Wow, then have some cold water, sweetheart.

527
00:39:49,841 --> 00:39:51,746
- Thanks.
- Sure.

528
00:39:52,108 --> 00:39:54,884
- Here, look what I made...
- I'm back.

529
00:39:54,991 --> 00:39:56,093
You're back already?

530
00:39:57,405 --> 00:39:58,733
Hello.

531
00:40:01,223 --> 00:40:02,308
Tiger?

532
00:40:02,377 --> 00:40:02,859
Yes, ma'am.

533
00:40:03,025 --> 00:40:04,656
I've missed you so much.

534
00:40:04,878 --> 00:40:06,432
- You're finally back.
- Yes, ma'am.

535
00:40:06,554 --> 00:40:07,573
How have you been?

536
00:40:07,829 --> 00:40:10,309
- I've been well. And you?
- Same here.

537
00:40:10,340 --> 00:40:12,465
Why didn't you tell me you were coming back?

538
00:40:13,143 --> 00:40:14,771
Wanted to surprise you.

539
00:40:16,986 --> 00:40:20,745
Now that Tiger's back, we should celebrate.

540
00:40:21,014 --> 00:40:22,589
A welcome-home feast.

541
00:40:23,097 --> 00:40:25,260
What would you like? I'll cook anything.

542
00:40:25,540 --> 00:40:27,017
Let's go all out.

543
00:40:28,637 --> 00:40:29,728
Omelet rice.

544
00:40:31,214 --> 00:40:32,880
You come back after all this time and want omelet rice?

545
00:40:33,014 --> 00:40:34,525
Let's do a barbecue instead.

546
00:40:34,872 --> 00:40:37,736
- Sound good? Let's have barbecue.
- Sounds good.

547
00:40:37,899 --> 00:40:40,579
- Sure.
- Then let's order some.

548
00:40:40,838 --> 00:40:41,936
How many sets should we get?

549
00:40:42,291 --> 00:40:44,463
No need to order too much.

550
00:40:44,634 --> 00:40:46,157
Oh no, it has to be a big one.

551
00:40:46,235 --> 00:40:47,438
Come here and give me another hug.

552
00:40:51,682 --> 00:40:54,336
Look at this place. The atmosphere is amazing.

553
00:40:55,677 --> 00:40:56,715
Damn.

554
00:40:57,318 --> 00:40:58,260
I think this is it.

555
00:41:03,709 --> 00:41:04,847
What are you guys looking at?

556
00:41:05,853 --> 00:41:07,874
Universities. Come look with us.

557
00:41:07,915 --> 00:41:08,751
Yeah.

558
00:41:08,856 --> 00:41:10,254
Faculty of Engineering,
Wabi Sabi University, Chiang Mai Campus.

559
00:41:10,728 --> 00:41:11,397
Dude.

560
00:41:12,339 --> 00:41:13,757
I think Chiang Mai's the one.

561
00:41:14,402 --> 00:41:15,973
The atmosphere is incredible.

562
00:41:16,237 --> 00:41:17,662
The campus is beautiful.

563
00:41:18,462 --> 00:41:20,162
And it's so green and peaceful.

564
00:41:20,893 --> 00:41:21,722
What do you think?

565
00:41:21,973 --> 00:41:23,148
Want to move to Chiang Mai with me?

566
00:41:24,370 --> 00:41:25,330
Sure.

567
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:28,365
When I asked if you'd go to Khon Kaen,

568
00:41:28,515 --> 00:41:29,564
you said sure too.

569
00:41:31,013 --> 00:41:32,546
North or south, I'm in.

570
00:41:35,082 --> 00:41:36,377
What about overseas?

571
00:41:36,521 --> 00:41:37,739
Like I said,

572
00:41:38,131 --> 00:41:40,980
I'm not just talking about Thailand. I mean anywhere.

573
00:41:41,296 --> 00:41:44,647
North Pole, South Pole, wherever.

574
00:41:50,280 --> 00:41:51,272
What's so funny, Dan?

575
00:41:51,900 --> 00:41:53,056
Nothing.

576
00:41:53,426 --> 00:41:55,582
Just thinking how attached you two are.

577
00:41:56,263 --> 00:41:58,525
No matter where you go, you're going together.

578
00:41:59,394 --> 00:42:00,937
That's what best friends do.

579
00:42:01,562 --> 00:42:02,302
Right, buddy?

580
00:42:07,050 --> 00:42:07,928
Chiang Mai, right?

581
00:42:09,197 --> 00:42:11,185
Yeah, I think Chiang Mai's the one.

582
00:42:13,962 --> 00:42:15,694
What about you, Dan? Decided yet?

583
00:42:19,277 --> 00:42:20,080
Yeah.

584
00:42:21,183 --> 00:42:21,881
Tiger.

585
00:42:22,456 --> 00:42:24,654
Can you tell us about studying abroad?

586
00:42:27,613 --> 00:42:28,982
You want to study overseas, Nue?

587
00:42:29,808 --> 00:42:30,717
Yeah.

588
00:42:31,040 --> 00:42:32,728
I want the experience.

589
00:42:33,265 --> 00:42:35,752
Meet talented people and improve my English.

590
00:42:36,345 --> 00:42:38,158
Step outside my comfort zone.

591
00:42:38,398 --> 00:42:40,592
Go somewhere nobody knows me.

592
00:42:40,774 --> 00:42:42,930
See how far I can go on my own.

593
00:42:43,554 --> 00:42:44,832
Then

594
00:42:45,204 --> 00:42:47,214
maybe try a big country like

595
00:42:47,718 --> 00:42:48,672
the U.S.?

596
00:42:49,388 --> 00:42:50,832
You'll meet all kinds of people there.

597
00:42:51,469 --> 00:42:52,520
Have you been there?

598
00:42:53,517 --> 00:42:55,367
For about three months, I think.

599
00:42:55,582 --> 00:42:56,850
Sometime during the last two years.

600
00:42:57,388 --> 00:42:58,832
Oh.

601
00:42:59,841 --> 00:43:01,145
America?

602
00:43:01,915 --> 00:43:03,167
That sounds pretty fun, actually.

603
00:43:04,028 --> 00:43:05,170
I'll think about it.

604
00:43:05,297 --> 00:43:06,139
Thanks, Tiger.

605
00:43:06,311 --> 00:43:07,158
No problem.

606
00:43:08,291 --> 00:43:09,518
Then let's all do our best together.

607
00:43:09,891 --> 00:43:12,462
But don't push yourselves so hard that you end up stressing yourselves out.

608
00:43:13,207 --> 00:43:14,961
Got it? Both of you.

609
00:43:15,874 --> 00:43:17,786
The more stressed and forced it feels, the worse it'll get.

610
00:43:19,754 --> 00:43:20,595
Ok.

611
00:43:32,517 --> 00:43:33,638
List of eligible applicants

612
00:44:32,392 --> 00:44:33,592
I'm about to confirm it.

613
00:44:33,761 --> 00:44:34,520
Go ahead.

614
00:44:35,943 --> 00:44:36,588
Let me pray first.

615
00:44:37,860 --> 00:44:39,583
Please let me get in.

616
00:44:39,797 --> 00:44:40,878
Any choice is fine.

617
00:44:47,721 --> 00:44:48,552
Admission Results

618
00:44:50,641 --> 00:44:52,143
Do you think I'll get in?

619
00:44:56,091 --> 00:44:57,155
It's almost time.

620
00:45:02,237 --> 00:45:04,170
Nao, stop pacing. You're giving me a headache.

621
00:45:05,989 --> 00:45:09,179
I'm nervous, okay? I've already failed twice.

622
00:45:09,570 --> 00:45:11,731
What if I don't get in this time either?

623
00:45:11,954 --> 00:45:13,656
You will. Trust me.

624
00:45:14,069 --> 00:45:16,878
Easy for you to say. You got in twice already.

625
00:45:17,816 --> 00:45:23,352
But promise me something. If I don't get in this time, don't give up your spot just to follow me again.

626
00:45:24,650 --> 00:45:25,216
Why?

627
00:45:25,997 --> 00:45:27,731
Why would you give up your place for me anyway?

628
00:45:35,931 --> 00:45:36,546
Oh!

629
00:45:38,699 --> 00:45:40,105
It's time. The results are out.

630
00:45:44,601 --> 00:45:46,152
- Ahh!
- Let me see.

631
00:45:48,444 --> 00:45:49,337
I'm so nervous.

632
00:45:50,328 --> 00:45:50,857
Mm.

633
00:45:53,706 --> 00:45:55,315
- What?
- I'm clicking it now.

634
00:45:58,140 --> 00:45:58,890
Do it.

635
00:46:09,670 --> 00:46:11,432
University and Program Confirmation Results

636
00:46:12,017 --> 00:46:13,977
Suer, I got in!

637
00:46:14,077 --> 00:46:16,610
I got in! I got in!

638
00:46:16,797 --> 00:46:20,374
- Are you okay, Duen?
- Mom, I got into university! I have a place now!

639
00:46:20,401 --> 00:46:23,371
Really? Congratulations, sweetheart. I'm so proud of you.

640
00:46:23,743 --> 00:46:25,481
- I'm so happy.
- Congratulations.

641
00:46:26,672 --> 00:46:27,574
You did great.

642
00:46:28,222 --> 00:46:29,638
What about Tiger?

643
00:46:30,299 --> 00:46:31,447
Yeah, what about your Suer?

644
00:46:32,405 --> 00:46:33,641
Enter your code.

645
00:46:34,293 --> 00:46:35,232
Let's see.

646
00:46:41,459 --> 00:46:43,514
Suer, you got in too.

647
00:46:43,811 --> 00:46:45,148
Just a different major.

648
00:46:46,093 --> 00:46:47,293
You're amazing.

649
00:46:48,540 --> 00:46:50,253
Then we definitely need to celebrate.

650
00:46:50,604 --> 00:46:53,041
And Dan got accepted in Boston too.

651
00:46:54,241 --> 00:46:57,145
- Dan, that's incredible.
- You did great too, Duen.

652
00:46:57,460 --> 00:46:58,423
Now that...

653
00:46:58,721 --> 00:47:00,102
I can finally stop worrying.

654
00:47:00,318 --> 00:47:02,120
Because Tiger will be there with you.

655
00:47:03,142 --> 00:47:05,604
If you two had to live far away all alone,

656
00:47:05,868 --> 00:47:07,327
I'd be worried sick.

657
00:47:08,506 --> 00:47:10,622
No need to worry, Mom. We'll be fine.

658
00:47:10,755 --> 00:47:11,702
Mm.

659
00:47:12,567 --> 00:47:13,837
So proud of you.

660
00:47:15,115 --> 00:47:16,933
Suer, what's wrong?

661
00:47:18,471 --> 00:47:19,920
You got in too.

662
00:47:20,222 --> 00:47:21,983
You're both going to Chiang Mai anyway, right?

663
00:47:22,925 --> 00:47:24,771
We'll go look for a dorm together, okay?

664
00:47:25,675 --> 00:47:27,622
- A dorm?
- Yeah, a dorm.

665
00:47:29,103 --> 00:47:29,931
Who are you staying with?

666
00:47:30,152 --> 00:47:31,186
You, obviously.

667
00:47:31,382 --> 00:47:32,822
Everyone else already has a place.

668
00:47:33,077 --> 00:47:35,057
It's just you and me left.

669
00:47:37,650 --> 00:47:39,776
- Or would you rather live alone?
- I'd rather live with you.

670
00:47:41,312 --> 00:47:42,429
That's what I like to hear.

671
00:47:44,557 --> 00:47:45,448
Ready?

672
00:47:46,120 --> 00:47:48,525
- Ready.
- Then let's celebrate!

673
00:47:48,586 --> 00:47:50,736
Moo Kratha!

674
00:47:50,902 --> 00:47:52,736
- Moo Kratha!
- Let's go!

675
00:47:52,798 --> 00:47:54,693
- Tiger, come on.
- Moo Kratha! Let's go!

676
00:47:54,912 --> 00:47:57,189
- Better help Mom set things up.
- Sure.

677
00:48:00,302 --> 00:48:01,242
Moo Kratha.

678
00:48:01,285 --> 00:48:02,370
Moo Kratha.

679
00:48:17,706 --> 00:48:18,423
Nue.

680
00:48:19,167 --> 00:48:20,297
Did Nao go to the market already?

681
00:48:20,871 --> 00:48:21,690
Yeah.

682
00:48:22,434 --> 00:48:23,678
He just left.

683
00:48:24,500 --> 00:48:25,170
Okay.

684
00:48:25,528 --> 00:48:26,570
Tiger.

685
00:48:27,385 --> 00:48:28,659
Can we talk for a minute?

686
00:48:28,817 --> 00:48:29,848
It won't take long.

687
00:48:37,296 --> 00:48:39,263
I've actually been looking for a chance to talk to you

688
00:48:39,308 --> 00:48:41,161
for a long time now.

689
00:48:42,540 --> 00:48:44,097
But it's been hard to find one.

690
00:48:44,933 --> 00:48:46,890
Because you're always glued to Duen's side.

691
00:48:48,154 --> 00:48:49,008
Uh-huh.

692
00:48:51,601 --> 00:48:52,826
How much do you like Duen?

693
00:48:55,456 --> 00:48:56,585
I don't like him.

694
00:48:57,536 --> 00:48:58,494
I love him.

695
00:48:59,271 --> 00:48:59,974
Why?

696
00:49:00,598 --> 00:49:01,551
I thought so.

697
00:49:02,072 --> 00:49:03,362
It's way beyond liking.

698
00:49:04,167 --> 00:49:05,245
You really love him.

699
00:49:05,632 --> 00:49:06,628
Then...

700
00:49:07,176 --> 00:49:08,200
How much do you love him?

701
00:49:10,183 --> 00:49:11,995
You might think I'm exaggerating if I tell you.

702
00:49:12,235 --> 00:49:13,068
You probably wouldn't believe me.

703
00:49:14,143 --> 00:49:14,989
I would.

704
00:49:15,262 --> 00:49:15,960
Go ahead.

705
00:49:19,688 --> 00:49:21,154
I'd die for Nao.

706
00:49:24,026 --> 00:49:25,518
That sounds about right.

707
00:49:27,130 --> 00:49:28,662
Tiger already proved it, too.

708
00:49:31,893 --> 00:49:32,848
What do you mean?

709
00:49:33,976 --> 00:49:34,955
It's just a guess.

710
00:49:35,680 --> 00:49:37,788
Actually, I wanted to thank you.

711
00:49:37,896 --> 00:49:38,894
Thank you so much.

712
00:49:39,200 --> 00:49:40,742
For loving my little brother.

713
00:49:41,358 --> 00:49:44,610
Duen may not be the type of kid people worry about.

714
00:49:44,808 --> 00:49:46,517
But as his older brother,

715
00:49:47,269 --> 00:49:48,853
I can't help worrying.

716
00:49:49,574 --> 00:49:51,800
And another thing, Duen is pretty innocent.

717
00:49:52,653 --> 00:49:54,708
Sometimes he's downright clueless.

718
00:49:55,109 --> 00:49:55,767
Right?

719
00:49:57,573 --> 00:49:58,318
True.

720
00:50:00,952 --> 00:50:02,174
About that guess...

721
00:50:02,641 --> 00:50:03,715
What made you think that?

722
00:50:06,511 --> 00:50:07,469
I just think

723
00:50:08,146 --> 00:50:09,835
it's a little too much of a coincidence.

724
00:50:11,508 --> 00:50:13,282
Two years ago,

725
00:50:13,536 --> 00:50:14,897
when we were kidnapped,

726
00:50:15,459 --> 00:50:18,115
was the same time Tiger went on exchange to Hong Kong.

727
00:50:19,454 --> 00:50:20,737
Someone like Tiger?

728
00:50:21,170 --> 00:50:22,952
Just disappearing without telling Duen?

729
00:50:24,487 --> 00:50:25,737
Even if you disappeared,

730
00:50:26,525 --> 00:50:27,828
it wouldn't be for long.

731
00:50:30,062 --> 00:50:31,328
So,

732
00:50:32,242 --> 00:50:34,023
there can only be one reason.

733
00:50:34,782 --> 00:50:36,558
You just couldn't contact him.

734
00:50:41,740 --> 00:50:46,764
Duen once told me you come from a pretty influential family.

735
00:50:47,377 --> 00:50:49,250
And you promised Duen

736
00:50:49,668 --> 00:50:51,327
You'd help us deal with Chat.

737
00:50:52,826 --> 00:50:55,223
You always keep the promises.

738
00:50:55,957 --> 00:50:57,050
But then,

739
00:50:57,580 --> 00:50:59,974
why have you ever asked about Chat?

740
00:51:03,613 --> 00:51:05,562
I think it's because

741
00:51:08,128 --> 00:51:09,705
You already took care of this matter.

742
00:51:16,082 --> 00:51:16,837
You're sharp.

743
00:51:18,189 --> 00:51:20,077
You figured all that out with so little information.

744
00:51:21,245 --> 00:51:24,740
It's only a guess. I don't know if it's true or not.

745
00:51:25,080 --> 00:51:26,370
But you don't have to tell me.

746
00:51:27,471 --> 00:51:29,066
Because you don't want other people to know.

747
00:51:32,845 --> 00:51:33,720
What about you?

748
00:51:35,481 --> 00:51:36,528
Is there anything you want to ask me?

749
00:51:39,082 --> 00:51:40,554
What do you think

750
00:51:41,475 --> 00:51:42,890
Nao feels about me?

751
00:51:45,619 --> 00:51:47,207
I knew you'd ask that.

752
00:51:47,925 --> 00:51:49,591
But I didn't think it'd be your first question.

753
00:51:50,287 --> 00:51:52,920
- And that you'd be so direct about it.
- The answer?

754
00:51:54,013 --> 00:51:55,160
In my opinion,

755
00:51:56,922 --> 00:51:58,155
Duen loves you.

756
00:52:00,737 --> 00:52:02,911
But I don't know what kind of love it is.

757
00:52:04,472 --> 00:52:05,635
Probably as a friend.

758
00:52:06,106 --> 00:52:07,840
He emphasizes that word so much.

759
00:52:08,536 --> 00:52:09,508
What else could it be?

760
00:52:09,951 --> 00:52:11,245
Maybe.

761
00:52:11,392 --> 00:52:13,571
Or maybe not.

762
00:52:14,662 --> 00:52:18,554
Love isn't limited to just being friends or lovers.

763
00:52:22,576 --> 00:52:23,893
Then what am I to him?

764
00:52:24,970 --> 00:52:26,365
Someone he can't live without.

765
00:52:30,108 --> 00:52:30,983
Tiger.

766
00:52:31,272 --> 00:52:32,967
You're someone Duen can't be without.

767
00:52:33,841 --> 00:52:34,850
That's all I can say.

768
00:52:40,878 --> 00:52:42,607
Before I leave for Boston,

769
00:52:43,035 --> 00:52:45,348
that's the one thing I wanted to tell you.

770
00:52:46,241 --> 00:52:46,854
And...

771
00:52:47,194 --> 00:52:48,521
when are you going to confess?

772
00:52:49,146 --> 00:52:51,020
You've been crushing on him all the way to college.

773
00:52:54,268 --> 00:52:55,469
If I tell him,

774
00:52:56,690 --> 00:52:57,795
what do you think?

775
00:53:00,023 --> 00:53:01,554
Hmm.

776
00:53:02,961 --> 00:53:03,752
I don't know.

777
00:53:06,699 --> 00:53:08,509
But no matter what the answer is,

778
00:53:08,817 --> 00:53:11,068
Duen would never cut you out of his life.

779
00:53:12,462 --> 00:53:13,232
Trust me.

780
00:53:16,697 --> 00:53:18,517
If I confess and he doesn't feel the same,

781
00:53:20,182 --> 00:53:21,680
I'd rather keep things the way they are.

782
00:53:24,142 --> 00:53:24,989
Seriously?

783
00:53:37,016 --> 00:53:38,029
Thank you.

784
00:53:40,783 --> 00:53:41,691
Thank you.

785
00:53:44,868 --> 00:53:45,927
Thank you.

786
00:53:49,742 --> 00:53:50,894
Congratulations.

787
00:53:50,986 --> 00:53:52,278
Thank you.

788
00:53:56,582 --> 00:53:57,736
Yes.

789
00:54:08,222 --> 00:54:09,875
Study hard, okay?

790
00:54:11,817 --> 00:54:12,810
Hey, Suer.

791
00:54:14,674 --> 00:54:16,640
We haven't taken a photo together yet. Want to?

792
00:54:17,290 --> 00:54:17,939
Sure.

793
00:54:23,088 --> 00:54:24,324
P'Duennao.

794
00:54:25,014 --> 00:54:27,127
Um... I...

795
00:54:27,282 --> 00:54:30,880
I've liked you for a long time.

796
00:54:31,032 --> 00:54:33,380
I don't know if you're seeing anyone.

797
00:54:34,882 --> 00:54:35,808
Thank you.

798
00:54:36,934 --> 00:54:39,374
Then... could I have your LINE?

799
00:54:40,860 --> 00:54:42,922
Sure.

800
00:54:42,979 --> 00:54:43,518
Here.

801
00:54:43,933 --> 00:54:44,977
What the hell is wrong with you, asshole?

802
00:54:46,275 --> 00:54:48,309
Do you have any plans this evening?

803
00:54:48,416 --> 00:54:50,168
I'm having mookata with my friends tonight.

804
00:54:54,034 --> 00:54:55,911
Here you go, kids.

805
00:54:56,200 --> 00:54:57,577
Wow.

806
00:54:58,128 --> 00:55:00,665
How is it? Tasty?

807
00:55:00,946 --> 00:55:03,349
- It's delicious, Mom.
- Eat as much as you want.

808
00:55:03,463 --> 00:55:05,493
If it's not enough, just tell me and I'll bring more.

809
00:55:05,567 --> 00:55:08,330
- Sure.
- Don't go home until you're full.

810
00:55:08,386 --> 00:55:09,928
Yes, ma'am.

811
00:55:09,940 --> 00:55:11,334
I'll go prepare some more things.

812
00:55:11,481 --> 00:55:13,880
- Want me to help, Mom?
- No, just sit and eat.

813
00:55:13,915 --> 00:55:15,099
Okay. Thank you.

814
00:55:15,174 --> 00:55:16,158
Sure.

815
00:55:16,931 --> 00:55:17,857
Hey.

816
00:55:18,579 --> 00:55:19,632
Let's go take some pictures.

817
00:55:19,945 --> 00:55:21,402
Sure.

818
00:55:23,299 --> 00:55:24,965
Come on.

819
00:55:25,038 --> 00:55:26,330
Come on, guys.

820
00:55:29,545 --> 00:55:31,971
- Ready?
- We finally made it.

821
00:55:32,088 --> 00:55:33,720
Yeah.

822
00:55:33,773 --> 00:55:35,082
I thought you weren't gonna make it.

823
00:55:35,321 --> 00:55:36,924
Hey, Tul, that's harsh.

824
00:55:37,392 --> 00:55:40,394
Look at me. I got into university, you know.

825
00:55:40,451 --> 00:55:42,854
Yeah, keep bragging.

826
00:55:43,217 --> 00:55:44,954
Hey Tul, I've been meaning to ask.

827
00:55:45,448 --> 00:55:47,451
Why'd you decide to go to Chiang Mai with us?

828
00:55:47,794 --> 00:55:48,914
I just wanted to.

829
00:55:49,309 --> 00:55:51,582
That's just how I am. Free-spirited.

830
00:55:51,760 --> 00:55:54,573
Too bad I won't be living with you guys.

831
00:55:54,705 --> 00:55:56,588
- It's okay.
- Don't be all mopey.

832
00:55:56,623 --> 00:55:58,177
We can always hang out later.

833
00:55:58,488 --> 00:55:59,469
Okay.

834
00:56:00,903 --> 00:56:02,088
Come on, let's take a picture.

835
00:56:02,167 --> 00:56:05,703
Back at school, people lined up to take pictures with Nue.

836
00:56:05,819 --> 00:56:07,056
He's really popular.

837
00:56:07,352 --> 00:56:08,345
Not that much.

838
00:56:09,087 --> 00:56:11,057
We've never taken a group photo together.

839
00:56:12,524 --> 00:56:13,112
Come here.

840
00:56:13,657 --> 00:56:16,025
One, two, three.

841
00:56:16,928 --> 00:56:18,158
One, two, three.

842
00:56:18,234 --> 00:56:19,031
I'm going to flood the shots.

843
00:56:19,877 --> 00:56:21,480
That's enough.

844
00:56:22,671 --> 00:56:23,986
Let's eat.

845
00:56:24,048 --> 00:56:25,225
The pork's burning.

846
00:56:28,220 --> 00:56:29,312
Hey, Suer.

847
00:56:31,828 --> 00:56:33,517
I didn't get a picture with you earlier.

848
00:56:33,906 --> 00:56:34,954
Wanna take one over there?

849
00:56:37,917 --> 00:56:39,140
Come on, let's do it.

850
00:56:46,961 --> 00:56:47,813
Nao.

851
00:56:49,146 --> 00:56:49,594
Hm?

852
00:56:50,737 --> 00:56:52,619
What about that girl?

853
00:56:54,712 --> 00:56:56,204
I think I'll give her a chance.

854
00:56:56,771 --> 00:56:58,285
She's pretty cute.

855
00:57:02,691 --> 00:57:03,786
Come on, let's take the picture.

856
00:57:12,048 --> 00:57:13,862
One, two, three.

857
00:57:17,506 --> 00:57:18,561
Smile.

858
00:57:22,614 --> 00:57:23,525
Alright, that's enough.

859
00:57:26,051 --> 00:57:27,300
Let's go eat mookata.

860
00:57:28,798 --> 00:57:29,613
I'll head back first.

861
00:57:33,737 --> 00:57:34,869
Hey, what are you guys doing?

862
00:57:35,454 --> 00:57:36,444
Eating pork.

863
00:57:36,998 --> 00:57:37,900
Hey.

864
00:57:38,976 --> 00:57:40,023
What about me, Nao...

865
00:57:43,059 --> 00:57:44,280
I like you too.

866
00:58:02,838 --> 00:58:03,539
Suer.

867
00:58:04,059 --> 00:58:06,613
Where have you been? Why didn't you tell me?

868
00:58:07,160 --> 00:58:08,232
Are you mad at me or something?

869
00:58:08,342 --> 00:58:11,816
Hey, Nao, are you still talking to that girl?

870
00:58:11,952 --> 00:58:13,705
Nao, let's take a picture together.

871
00:58:14,037 --> 00:58:15,459
One, two, three.

872
00:58:15,574 --> 00:58:17,152
Don't you want to confess your feelings?

873
00:58:17,401 --> 00:58:19,414
If I tell him and he doesn't feel the same way,

874
00:58:19,451 --> 00:58:20,955
I'd rather keep things the way they are.

875
00:58:22,622 --> 00:58:26,939
No matter what the answer is, Duen would never cut you out of his life.
